[{"id":"VR803483","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A parallel-plate capacitor with plates of area <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>A</mi></math></span></span> and plate separation <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"d\"><math alttext=\"d\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>d</mi></math></span></span> is attached to a battery and given a charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Q\"><math alttext=\"Q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>Q</mi></math></span></span>. The potential energy stored in the capacitor is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"U sub 1\"><math alttext=\"U sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>U</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mstyle></math></span></span>. The capacitor is then detached from the battery and then the plates are pulled apart to a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 d\"><math alttext=\"2 d\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn><mi>d</mi></math></span></span>. The potential energy stored in the capacitor is now <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"U sub 2\"><math alttext=\"U sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>U</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mstyle></math></span></span>. Which of the following correctly describes the ratio of the potential energies <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction U sub 1 over U sub 2\"><math alttext=\"the fraction U sub 1 over U sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>U</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mstyle><msub><mi>U</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfrac></mstyle></math></span></span>?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR803483_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"one fourth\"><math alttext=\"one fourth\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mn>1</mn></mstyle><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"one half\"><math alttext=\"one half\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mn>1</mn></mstyle><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mn>2</mn></mstyle></mfrac></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 over 1\"><math alttext=\"2 over 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mn>2</mn></mstyle><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mn>1</mn></mstyle></mfrac></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"4 over 1\"><math alttext=\"4 over 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mn>4</mn></mstyle><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mn>1</mn></mstyle></mfrac></mstyle></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":1}]